sequentialTasks.description:
The comment block at `internal/command/pr_split.go:496` says:
```
// Verification shells are standalone CaptureSession objects (see
// pr_split_06b_verify_shell.js) — they are NOT attached to tuiMux.
```
This is FALSE. Verify sessions are now registered with tuiMux via `tuiMux.register()`. The `_buildVerifyProxy` in `pr_split_13_tui.js` explicitly calls `tuiMux.snapshot(sessionID)`, `tuiMux.activate(sessionID)`, `tuiMux.input()`, and `tuiMux.unregister(sessionID)`. Fix the comment to accurately describe the current architecture: verify sessions are registered with tuiMux and accessed through a pinned SessionID proxy.
